Courtesy #DStv403 JOHANNESBURG -Social Development Minister Lindiwe Zulu says over 58,000 households and close to 250,000 people have already started receiving food parcels. The food parcels have been delivered through the department’s Community Nutrition Development Centres. President Cyril Ramaphosa tasked his administration to help those who are going to bed hungry. READ: 250,000 food parcels to be distributed during lockdown: Ramaphosa "In total, over 58 000 households and close to 250 000 people have already started receiving these food parcels through our community nutrition development centres, which we normally call the CNDC's. Our provinces are coordinating this and we are looking at up-scaling this programme so that we respond effectively to the call by the president that no South African should be left hungry", said Zulu. Zulu also says the special COVID-19 Social Relief Grant will be available to South Africans, permanent residents and refugees registered on the Home Affairs system who are resident within the Republic's borders. Our political editor Vuyo Mvoko is following the story. Courtesy #DStv403 The water and sanitation minister admits the government is still struggling to deliver water to communities during the lockdown. Lindiwe Sisulu promised adequate water supply to areas without running taps. This is an effort to help stop the spread of COVID-19. So far, the number of confirmed COVID-19 cases in South Africa has risen to 4,996 and the death toll has increased to 93. - Coronavirus Hotline Number: 0800 029 999 from 8am to 4pm, Monday to Friday Help protect your loved ones by sharing this official South African government COVID-19 service with your family, friends and community. Send HI to 0600 123 456 on WhatsApp. The NICD has another Clinician Hotline to improve #COVID19 communication and support for healthcare providers. The Clinician Hotline is 0800 11 1131, operating 24 hrs. The Public Hotline is 0800 029 999 also operating 24hrs.